p2
VThe uniqueness of music
p3
sVnews
p4
VS. Salai Lakshana presented a lively vocal concert at the monthly music festival of the Tiruchi Tamil Isai Sangam, held at the Tamil Sangam premises in Tiruchi recently. She was accompanied by Tiruchi Govindarajan on the violin, Thanjavur G. Sankarasubramaniam on the mridangam and Malaikottai R.M. Deenadayalu on the morsing.L. N. Lakshmanan, industrialist and president of the Tiruchi Tamil Isai Sangam, presided over the concert. Rajavelu Shenbagavalli, founder of the Srirangam based Shenbaga Tamil Arangu, was the chief guest.Timeless appealSpeaking on the occasion Mr. Rajavelu said, &#8220;Music has no caste or religion; it plays a key role in bringing solace to the people suffering from all sorts of worries. The unique quality of music is, it attracts young and old alike and could be listened to and enjoyed round the clock.&#8221;Rajavelu commended the Tirucih Tamil Isai Sangam for promoting Tamil music and art through such monthly music festivals.&#8220;These programmes have also provided a good opportunity to budding musicians,&#8221; he added.K. Rangarajan, secretary, Tiruchi Tamil Isai Sangam, N. Mohan, its vice-president, offered felicitations.Kesavan, a patron of the Tamil Isai Sangam, who sponsored the programme, was honoured on the occasion.
